Usage: jpipe <command> [options]

A lightweight C pipe-to-JSON logger designed for high-performance stream capture and extensible metadata injection.

Commands:
  run                Process data with configurable options.
  version            Display version information.
  help               Show this help message.

Global Options:
  -q, --quiet        Display less output (suppress non-critical logs).
  -C, --no-color     Disable colored output.
  
Environment Variables:
  NO_COLOR           If set (to any value), disables colored output.
                     See https://no-color.org/ for details.

Use 'jpipe <command> --help' for more information on a specific command.

Examples:
  # Capture stream with 1MB chunks to a specific directory
  cat data.log | jpipe run -c 1mb -o /tmp/output

  # High-throughput capture with a larger buffer
  tail -f /var/log/syslog | jpipe run -b 128 -c 64kb

Documentation & Issues:
  https://github.com/scoekmen/jpipe
